{"kind":"article","topicSections":[{"title":"Related","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SharedFolder","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawTemplate"],"anchor":"Related"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],"anchor":"Guides"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"role":"collectionGroup","title":"Running OpenClaw in Virtual Machines","roleHeading":"API Collection"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/openclawguide"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/openclaw.ai","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is an open-source self-hosted AI assistant"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that connects to Claude, GPT-4, Gemini, and other models. Running OpenClaw"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in macOS VMs with Spooktacular gives you:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolation"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — each instance has its own macOS environment, API keys,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and workspace. A misconfigured agent can’t affect the other.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2 instances per Mac"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — Apple Silicon’s 2-VM kernel limit maps","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"perfectly to running a pair of agents (e.g., work + personal,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or production + staging).","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Snapshots"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — save a working OpenClaw configuration, experiment,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and roll back if something breaks.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Kubernetes-managed","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — scale OpenClaw instances across a fleet","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of Macs using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MacOSVMPool"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Prerequisites","type":"heading","text":"Prerequisites"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS 14+ on the host","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular installed ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"brew install --cask spooktacular"},{"text":")","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"API key from Anthropic, OpenAI, or Google","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Quick-Start-Two-OpenClaw-Instances","type":"heading","text":"Quick Start: Two OpenClaw Instances"},{"level":3,"anchor":"1-Create-the-first-VM","type":"heading","text":"1. Create the first VM"},{"syntax":"bash","code":["spook create openclaw-work --from-ipsw latest \\","    --cpu 4 --memory 8 --disk 32 \\","    --network nat \\","    --user-data .\/setup-openclaw.sh \\","    --provision disk-inject"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"anchor":"2-Clone-for-the-second-instance","type":"heading","text":"2. Clone for the second instance"},{"syntax":"bash","code":["spook clone openclaw-work openclaw-personal"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The clone takes ~50ms (APFS copy-on-write). Each VM gets a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unique machine identifier automatically."}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"3-Start-both","type":"heading","text":"3. Start both"},{"syntax":"bash","code":["spook start openclaw-work --headless","spook start openclaw-personal --headless"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both VMs boot and run OpenClaw independently. Each listens"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on its own IP address, port 18789."}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"4-Check-status","type":"heading","text":"4. Check status"},{"syntax":"bash","code":["spook list","spook ip openclaw-work","spook ip openclaw-personal"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"anchor":"User-Data-Script-for-OpenClaw","type":"heading","text":"User-Data Script for OpenClaw"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a script that installs and configures OpenClaw automatically:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["#!\/bin\/bash","# setup-openclaw.sh — installs OpenClaw in a macOS VM","","set -euo pipefail","","# Install Homebrew (if not present)","if ! command -v brew &>\/dev\/null; then","    \/bin\/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/Homebrew\/install\/HEAD\/install.sh)\"","    eval \"$(\/opt\/homebrew\/bin\/brew shellenv)\"","fi","","# Install Node.js 24","brew install node@24","echo 'export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"' >> ~\/.zshrc","export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"","","# Install OpenClaw","npm install -g openclaw@latest","","# Run onboard with daemon installation","# (The API key should be set via environment variable or","#  injected via the shared folder)","openclaw onboard --install-daemon","","echo \"OpenClaw installed and running on port 18789\""],"syntax":"bash"},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For production deployments, pass the API key via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a shared folder or environment variable rather than"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"hardcoding it in the script."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Passing-API-Keys-Securely","type":"heading","text":"Passing API Keys Securely"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use a shared folder to deliver configuration without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"embedding secrets in the script:"}]},{"syntax":"bash","code":["# On the host: create a config directory","mkdir -p ~\/openclaw-configs\/work","cat > ~\/openclaw-configs\/work\/openclaw.json << 'EOF'","{","    \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250514\",","    \"anthropicApiKey\": \"sk-ant-your-key-here\"","}","EOF","","# Create VM with shared folder","spook create openclaw-work --from-ipsw latest \\","    --share ~\/openclaw-configs\/work:config:ro \\","    --user-data .\/setup-openclaw.sh"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the setup script, copy the config from the shared folder:"}]},{"syntax":"bash","code":["# Inside setup-openclaw.sh","mkdir -p ~\/.openclaw","cp \"\/Volumes\/My Shared Files\/openclaw.json\" ~\/.openclaw\/openclaw.json","openclaw config validate"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Kubernetes-OpenClaw-Fleet","type":"heading","text":"Kubernetes: OpenClaw Fleet"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy OpenClaw instances across multiple Macs using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the Kubernetes operator:"}]},{"syntax":"yaml","code":["apiVersion: spooktacular.io\/v1alpha1","kind: MacOSVMPool","metadata:","  name: openclaw-agents","  namespace: ai","spec:","  replicas: 2","  image: ghcr.io\/spooktacular\/macos:15.4","","  provisioning:","    mode: disk-inject","    userData: |","      #!\/bin\/bash","      brew install node@24","      export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"","      npm install -g openclaw@latest","      mkdir -p ~\/.openclaw","      # Config injected via K8s secret → shared folder","      cp \"\/Volumes\/My Shared Files\/openclaw.json\" ~\/.openclaw\/","      openclaw onboard --install-daemon","","  resources:","    cpu: 4","    memory: 8Gi","    disk: 32Gi","","  network:","    mode: nat"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each Mac in the fleet runs 2 OpenClaw VMs. Ten Macs ="},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"20 OpenClaw instances."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Networking-Between-Instances","type":"heading","text":"Networking Between Instances"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your OpenClaw instances need to communicate (e.g.,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a coordinator agent delegating to worker agents):"}]},{"syntax":"bash","code":["spook create openclaw-coordinator --from-ipsw latest --network nat","spook create openclaw-worker --from-ipsw latest --network nat"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"NAT networking lets the VMs reach each other via their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"DHCP-assigned IPs and the host Mac. The coordinator can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reach the worker’s gateway on port 18789. Use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" if you need to prevent internet"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"access entirely, communicating through shared folders"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and the VirtIO socket instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For internet access + inter-VM communication, use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"NAT networking — both VMs can reach each other via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their NAT-assigned IPs."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Resource-Planning","type":"heading","text":"Resource Planning"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Setup"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"CPU"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Memory"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Disk"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Notes"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cloud models only"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"4 cores"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"4 GB"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"16 GB"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Minimal — OpenClaw is lightweight"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cloud + light local models"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"4 cores"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"8 GB"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"32 GB"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ollama with small models"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Heavy local models (Llama 3)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"6 cores"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"16 GB"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"64 GB"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Needs unified memory"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since macOS VMs share the host’s unified memory via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the Virtualization framework, the GPU (Metal) is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"available inside the VM for local model inference."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Monitoring","type":"heading","text":"Monitoring"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Check OpenClaw health in each VM:"}]},{"syntax":"bash","code":["# From the host","spook ssh openclaw-work -- \"openclaw status\"","spook ssh openclaw-personal -- \"openclaw status\"","","# Or via the gateway API","curl http:\/\/$(spook ip openclaw-work):18789\/health","curl http:\/\/$(spook ip openclaw-personal):18789\/health"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Snapshots","type":"heading","text":"Snapshots"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Save a working OpenClaw configuration before making changes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The VM must be stopped to take or restore a disk-level snapshot:"}]},{"syntax":"bash","code":["spook stop openclaw-work","spook snapshot openclaw-work pre-upgrade","spook start openclaw-work --headless","# ... make changes, install new version ...","# If something breaks:","spook stop openclaw-work","spook restore openclaw-work pre-upgrade","spook start openclaw-work --headless"],"type":"codeListing"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run two isolated OpenClaw AI agent instances on a single Mac — each with its own workspace, channels, and API keys."}],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/NetworkMode/isolated":{"title":"NetworkMode.isolated","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/networkmode\/isolated","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"isolated","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"No network connectivity.","type":"text"}]},"https://openclaw.ai":{"url":"https:\/\/openclaw.ai","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OpenClaw"}],"title":"OpenClaw","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/openclaw.ai"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/KubernetesGuide":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage macOS virtual machines as Kubernetes resources using the MacOSVM custom resource definition."}],"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/kubernetesguide","kind":"article","title":"Kubernetes Integration","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit":{"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Create and manage macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon.","type":"text"}],"title":"SpooktacularKit"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/OpenClawTemplate":{"title":"OpenClawTemplate","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/openclawtemplate","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawTemplate","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OpenClawTemplate","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OpenClawTemplate","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Generates user-data scripts for OpenClaw AI agent VMs."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GitHubActionsGuide":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run self-hosted macOS GitHub Actions runners in Spooktacular VMs with ephemeral isolation and automatic scaling."}],"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/githubactionsguide","kind":"article","title":"Configuring GitHub Actions Runners","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/BlueBubblesGuide":{"role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/bluebubblesguide","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Set up a BlueBubbles iMessage server in a macOS VM — a dramatically simpler alternative to VMware on Windows."}],"title":"Running BlueBubbles iMessage Server"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/EC2MacDeployment":{"role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/ec2macdeployment","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac dedicated hosts to double your macOS CI capacity."}],"title":"Deploying on EC2 Mac"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/SharedFolder":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A directory shared between the host and the virtual machine."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/sharedfolder","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SharedFolder","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"SharedFolder","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SharedFolder","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SharedFolder","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GettingStarted":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes."}],"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted","kind":"article","title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/JenkinsGuide":{"title":"Configuring Jenkins Nodes","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/jenkinsguide","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[{"text":"Run Jenkins build agents in Spooktacular VMs for iOS and macOS CI\/CD.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/ProvisioningMode":{"type":"topic","title":"ProvisioningMode","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/provisioningmode","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ProvisioningMode"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ProvisioningMode"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The strategy for executing a user-data script on a VM."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/RemoteDesktop":{"type":"topic","title":"Remote Desktop Access","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/remotedesktop","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect to Spooktacular VMs via VNC for remote development, QA testing, and design review."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/MLWorkloads":{"role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/mlworkloads","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","abstract":[{"text":"Run ML training and inference on Apple Silicon GPUs inside Spooktacular virtual machines.","type":"text"}],"title":"Machine Learning Workloads"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/CLIReference":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage macOS virtual machines from the terminal with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI."}],"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/clireference","kind":"article","title":"Using the spook Command-Line Interface","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/Versioning":{"title":"Versioning & Release Schedule","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/versioning","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[{"text":"Understand what version numbers mean and what to expect from each release.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/NetworkMode":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The network configuration mode for a virtual machine."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/networkmode","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"NetworkMode"}],"title":"NetworkMode","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"NetworkMode"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/VirtualMachineSpecification":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The hardware specification for a virtual machine."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/virtualmachinespecification","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VirtualMachineSpecification"}],"title":"VirtualMachineSpecification","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VirtualMachineSpecification","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification","type":"topic"}}}